- Change the project structure
- Add any components
- Install additional packages

## Files
- components/PartnerLogos.tsx (modify)

## What to do
The requestAnimationFrame loop in PartnerLogos runs continuously even when the element is scrolled off-screen, wasting CPU cycles. Add an IntersectionObserver to pause the animation when not visible.

Add a `visibleRef` boolean ref. Create an IntersectionObserver in the useEffect that watches the outer container. When not intersecting, skip the rAF loop.

```tsx
const visibleRef = useRef(true);

useEffect(() => {
  const row = rowRef.current;
  if (!row) return;

  // Observe visibility
  const container = row.parentElement;
  if (container) {
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      ([entry]) => {
        visibleRef.current = entry.isIntersecting;
      },
      { threshold: 0 }
    );
    observer.observe(container);

    const animate = () => {
      if (visibleRef.current) {
        offsetRef.current += 0.5;
        const totalWidth = row.scrollWidth;
        const oneThird = totalWidth / 3;
        if (offsetRef.current >= oneThird) {
          offsetRef.current = 0;
        }
        row.style.transform = `translateX(-${offsetRef.current}px)`;
      }
      rafRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    };

    rafRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);

    return () => {
      observer.disconnect();
      if (rafRef.current !== null) {
        cancelAnimationFrame(rafRef.current);
      }
    };
  }
}, []);
```

Note: We still keep the rAF loop running (just skipping the transform update) so the animation resumes instantly when scrolled back into view.

## Dont
- Do NOT change the animation speed or behavior when visible
- Do NOT add any external dependencies
- Do NOT change the visual output

## Files
- next.config.ts (modify)

## What to do
The next.config.ts is empty. Add image configuration with remotePatterns for any external image domains that might be used, and ensure local images work correctly.

```ts
import type { NextConfig } from "next";

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      {
        protocol: "https",
        hostname: "hypercerts.org",
      },
      {
        protocol: "https",
        hostname: "app.hypercerts.org",
      },
    ],
  },
};

export default nextConfig;
```

## Dont
- Do NOT add any other config options
- Do NOT add domains that are not related to hypercerts

## Files
- app/layout.tsx (modify)
- app/sitemap.ts (create)
- app/robots.ts (create)

## What to do

### 1. JSON-LD structured data in layout.tsx
Add a <script type="application/ld+json"> tag inside the <head> (or as a child of <html> before <body>) with Organization schema:

```tsx
<script
  type="application/ld+json"
  dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{
    __html: JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Organization",
      name: "Hypercerts Foundation",
      url: "https://hypercerts.org",
      logo: "https://hypercerts.org/img/hypercerts_logo_horizontal.svg",
      sameAs: [
        "https://twitter.com/hypercerts",
        "https://github.com/hypercerts-org",
      ],
    }),
  }}
/>
```

Place this as the first child inside <body>, before <Header />.

### 2. Sitemap (app/sitemap.ts)
Create a Next.js metadata sitemap:
```ts
import type { MetadataRoute } from "next";

export default function sitemap(): MetadataRoute.Sitemap {
  return [
    {
      url: "https://hypercerts.org",
      lastModified: new Date(),
      changeFrequency: "weekly",
      priority: 1,
    },
  ];
}
```

### 3. Robots (app/robots.ts)
Create a Next.js metadata robots file:
```ts
import type { MetadataRoute } from "next";

export default function robots(): MetadataRoute.Robots {
  return {
    rules: {
      userAgent: "*",
      allow: "/",
    },
    sitemap: "https://hypercerts.org/sitemap.xml",
  };
}
```

## Dont
- Do NOT add Google Analytics or any tracking scripts
- Do NOT modify existing metadata fields
- Do NOT add pages that dont exist to the sitemap

## Files
- app/not-found.tsx (create)
- app/error.tsx (create)

## What to do

### 1. not-found.tsx
Create a custom 404 page that matches the site design:

```tsx
import Link from "next/link";

export default function NotFound() {
  return (
    <main className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-white">
      <div className="text-center px-6">
        <h1 className="font-display text-display-1 max-sm:text-[80px] text-brand-black">
          404
        </h1>
        <p className="font-body text-body-lg text-ui-grey-dark mt-4 mb-8">
          This page could not be found.
        </p>
        <Link
          href="/"
          className="inline-block bg-brand-black text-brand-white px-8 py-3 rounded-brand text-body-lg font-medium hover:bg-brand-navy transition"
        >
          Go home
        </Link>
      </div>
    </main>
  );
}
```

### 2. error.tsx
Create a custom error boundary. This MUST be a client component:

```tsx
"use client";

export default function Error({
  reset,
}: {
  error: Error & { digest?: string };
  reset: () => void;
}) {
  return (
    <main className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-white">
      <div className="text-center px-6">
        <h1 className="font-display text-display-2 text-brand-black">
          Something went wrong
        </h1>
        <p className="font-body text-body-lg text-ui-grey-dark mt-4 mb-8">
          An unexpected error occurred.
        </p>
        <button
          onClick={reset}
          className="inline-block bg-brand-black text-brand-white px-8 py-3 rounded-brand text-body-lg font-medium hover:bg-brand-navy transition"
        >
          Try again
        </button>
      </div>
    </main>
  );
}
```

## Dont
- Do NOT add any external dependencies
- Do NOT add complex layouts — keep it minimal
- Do NOT import Header/Footer (they are in the layout and will render automatically)
